estions and discussion. Participants will be able to register for either the entire three-day meeting or for any combination of individual one-day blocks.</p><p>　　<strong>OBJECTIVES</strong></p><p>　　The principal objective of this activity is to identify areas of diagnostic difficulties and challenges in everyday surgical pathology and cytopathology practice, and to provide expert insight on selected topics through different educational formats. Educational experience is further enhanced through a collegial contact and one-on-one interaction throughout the course. As identified through recent publications and other data gathering efforts, the topics selected each year reflect areas in which substantial information and progress has been made. The topics of discussion also focus on areas in which there is significant difficulty in interpretation of pathological features. In general terms, we expect that at the end of this course, the participants will:</p><p>　　■reduce occurrence of common mistakes and pitfalls in the diagnosis of genitourinary, breast, gynecological, gastrointestinal, hepatobiliary, hematolymphoid, pulmonary, and soft tissue diseases （see program for specific diseases in the current course） in everyday surgical pathology;</p><p>　　■improve diagnostic accuracy with mimickers of specific diseases in each specialty;</p><p>　　■interpret special studies that will allow easier differential diagnosis;</p><p>　　■improve ability to identify the pertinent histopathological characteristics of diseases to allow unequivocal diagnosis;</p><p>　　■use new and additional components of the pathology report to improve its clinical value;</p><p>　　■integrate the recent changes/modifications in the pathological classification of diseases or lesions.</p><p><br/></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img src=\"/ueditor/net/upload/image/20170320/6362563198494454606655782.png\" style=\"\" title=\"1.png\"/></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img src=\"http://h.91360.com:8800/ueditor/net/upload/image/20170320/6362563198474043666184733.png\" title=\"2.png\" style=\"white-space: normal;\"/></p><p>&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong> 详情见附件下载。</strong><br/></p>','','','','0',NULL,'2017-05-19 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'0','0','0','0','0','0','2017-03-20 18:40:21',NULL,'University of California San Francisco','','','UCSF','(415) 476-5808','UCSF Office of Continuing Medical Education P.O. B','0','2017-03-20 18:40:21','1','0','','',NULL,'33RD ANNUAL Current Issues in Anatomic Pathology University of California San Francisco  conference','This annual course addresses a wide range of topics in anatomic pathology and explores new and evolving areas in the diagnosis and analysis of disease. It aims to provide the latest practical and theoretical information that will aid the practicing pathologist in solving those problems most often encountered in the anatomic pathology laboratory. An audience response system will facilitate questions and discussion. Participants will be able to register for either the entire three-day meeting or f',NULL,NULL,'0','2'), ('385','关于举办常用特殊染色技术新进展及实践操作培训班通知','2017-07-28 00:00:00','2017-07-30 00:00:00','0','30','367','北京路292号','<p>　　为了进一步提高病理科技师、医师在日对常用特殊染色技术理论知识、实践操作、诊断及鉴别诊断中的应用、染色中室内质量控制、染液的自行配制及化学试剂的处置与管理等水平。由中国医学装备协会病理装备技术专业委员会、国家卫生和计划生育委员会病理质控评价中心主办，云南省第三人民医院病理科承办的国家级继续医学教育项目《常用特殊染色技术新进展及实践操作培训班》[项目编号：2017-01-04-097（国）]，将于<span style=\"color: rgb(255, 0, 0);\"><strong>2017年7月28日-30日</strong></span>在云南省昆明市举行。会议将邀请中山大学附一院梁英杰老师、北京协和医院王德田老师、北京大学医学部王盛兰老师、南京军区南京总医院马恒辉老师、南方医科大学南方医院张进华老师、浙江大学附一院丁伟老师、云南省二院周虹老师及云南省三院孙涛老师等省内外专家进行专题学术讲座，同时将进行部分特殊染色染液配制及验证、几种常用特殊染色在技术专家现场指导染色操作、带教阅片、经验交流和相互讨论，旨在巩固和提升参会学员对几种常用特殊染色理论、实践及应用等水平。现将有关事项通知如下：</p><p>　　<strong>一、报到时间：<span style=\"color: rgb(255, 0, 0);\">2017年7月28日14:30-18:00（提交2寸免冠照片一张，证书用）</span></strong></p><p>　　<strong>二、会议时间：</strong><span style=\"color: rgb(255, 0, 0);\"><strong>2017年7月29日-2017年7月30日</strong></span></p><p>　　三<strong>、报到地点：</strong>云南省第三人民医院病理科（云南省昆明市北京路292号）</p><p>　　<strong>四、会议地点：</strong>云南省第三人民医院住院部16楼1605会议室</p><p>　　<strong>五、会议内容：</strong></p><p>　　（一）专题学术讲座</p><p>　　1、特殊染色在病理诊断中的应用</p><p>　　2、特殊染色与免疫组化相结合在鉴别诊断中的应用</p><p>　　3、特殊染色目前应用现状及未来发展前景</p><p>　　4、如何染出一张好的特殊染色切片</p><p>　　5、抗酸、弹性纤维、新型隐球菌等染色试剂配制及操作要点</p><p>　　6、六胺银、淀粉样变性染色的应用及操作要点</p><p>　　7、特殊染色在肾脏穿刺组织中的应用</p><p>　　8、特殊染色室内质量控制及总结</p><p>　　9、病理技术全流程质量控制的重要性</p><p>　　10、病理科化学试剂的管理与处置</p><p>　　（二）染液自行配制及试剂验证操作（包括：网状纤维等）</p><p>　　（三）几种常用特殊染色现场操作、带教阅片</p><p>　　包括：抗酸染色、弹性纤维染色、真菌（新型隐球菌）染色、网状纤维染色等</p><p>　　<strong>六、培训费用：</strong></p><p>　　培训班费用900元/人，含注册费、操作培训费、资料费、餐费，会议期间食宿统一安推，住宿费、交通费自理，回单位报销。</p><p>　　<strong>七、报名方式：</strong></p><p>　　1、参会回执参照附件一以电子版形式发至279722756@qq.com邮箱报名。</p><p>　　2、以短信形式、电话形式报名。</p><p>　　3、以微信形式报名，微俏号：13759416387。</p><p>　　以上述其中一种形式报名即可，<span style=\"color: rgb(255, 0, 0);\"><strong>报名截止日期为2017年7月24日。</strong></span></p><p>　　<strong>八、其他事宜：</strong></p><p>　　1、培训结束后，将授予国家级继续医学教育I类学分10分。云南省内统一采用二维码授予电子学分，省外上网打印学分。</p><p>　　2、培训结束后，实践操作考试合格者将颁发中国医学装备协会病理装备技术专业委员会、国家卫生和计划生育委员会病理质控评价中心培训合格证书。</p><p>　　3、相关日程等其他具体事项详见第二轮通知。</p><p>　　<strong>九、联系方式：</strong></p><p>　　联系人：徐开军，孙涛</p><p>　　电话：13759416387，15925208806，0871-63198478。</p><p><br/></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>报名回执</strong></p><p><br/></p><table><tbody><tr class=\"firstRow\"><td width=\"96\" valign=\"top\" style=\"word-break: break-all;\">姓名：</td><td width=\"96\" valign=\"top\" style=\"word-break: break-all;\"><br/></td><td width=\"96\" valign=\"top\" style=\"word-break: break-all;\">性别：</td><td width=\"96\" valign=\"top\" style=\"word-break: break-all;\"><br/></td><td width=\"96\" valign=\"top\" style=\"word-break: break-all;\">职称：</td><td width=\"96\" valign=\"top\" style=\"word-break: break-all;\"><br/></td></tr><tr><td width=\"96\" valign=\"top\" style=\"word-break: break-all;\">工作单位：</td><td width=\"96\" valign=\"top\" style=\"word-break: break-all;\"><br/></td><td width=\"96\" valign=\"top\" style=\"word-break: break-all;\"><br/></td><td width=\"96\" valign=\"top\" style=\"word-break: break-all;\">单位地址：</td><td width=\"96\" v